          <p class="supertitle">Full Time / New York, New York 10001</p>
  <h1>Ruby Developer</h1>

  <div class="columns generic ">
    <div class="column main">
      <p>Category: Web Development</p>

<p>Ruby Developer</p>

<p>The Daily Beast is hiring a team of experienced devs to help our product team reach several ambitious goals. Developers will have a true sense of ownership of the products, a great work environment, and a team of peers focused on getting things done while maintaining a great work/life balance.</p>

<p>Ruby Developers will help architect and implement a world-class publishing system (along with other products) for a growing, renowned news, politics, opinion, and entertainment site. Days will consist of hacking on the products, participating in code reviews, brainstorming with the product design and management team, and helping tests turn from red to green.</p>

<p>Technologies on our radar include:</p>

<p>Ruby, PHP5 (legacy system we are porting to Ruby)</p>

<p>Sinatra, Rails (3), Rack</p>

<p>Cucumber, RSpec</p>

<p>MongoDB, MySQL5</p>

<p>Memcached, Redis</p>

<p>HTML5, CSS, JQuery</p>

<p>Android</p>

<p>EC2, AWS</p>

<p>git</p>

<p>iOS4</p>

<p>Familiarity with REST design principles; web security; common frameworks &amp; patterns; and UX best practices are greatly appreciated. A passion for behavior-driven development, continuous integration, continuous deployment, and agile development will fit in well.</p>

<p>All candidates should be able to show at least one Rails-based site currently in production and discuss its architecture. Candidates with demonstrable OSS work (GitHub username, please!) will move to the top of the stack.</p>

<p>Compensation is competitive, the environment is very fun and interesting, and the entire company is passionate about the product.</p>
</div><!-- /.column.main -->

